29 §2355. Functions and responsibilities; Coordinated Use of Resources for Recreation,
30 Economy, Navigation, and Transportation Authority Board
31 A. The board shall:
32 (1) Represent the state's position on policy relative to the protection,
33 conservation, enhancement, and management of the upland non coastal area of the
34 state through oversight of integrated projects and programs and by addressing
35 activities which could significantly affect integrated projects and programs, all
36 consistent with the legislative intent as expressed in this Title.
37 (2) Develop, coordinate, make reports on, and provide oversight for a
38 comprehensive upland non coastal area master plan and annual plans, working in
39 conjunction with state agencies, political subdivisions, including flood protection
40 authorities, levee districts, and federal agencies. The master plan shall include a
41 comprehensive strategy addressing the protection, conservation, enhancement, and
42 management of the upland area through the construction and management of
43 integrated projects and programs, all consistent with the legislative intent as
44 expressed in this Chapter. The annual plan shall be developed as the annual
45 implementation of the comprehensive master plan and shall be submitted to the
46 legislature for approval as set forth in R.S. 38:2354. The annual plan shall include
47 a description and status of all projects and programs pertaining to the authority's
48 mission, including privately funded projects or plans, and addressing those activities
49 which significantly affect projects set forth in the plan, all consistent with the
50 legislative intent as expressed in this Title.
51 (3) Submit to the House Committee on Natural Resources and Environment
52 and the Senate Committee on Natural Resources and the House Committee on
53 Transportation, Highways and Public Works and the Senate Committee on
54 Transportation, Highways and Public Works meeting jointly, the integrated plans
55 developed pursuant to R.S. 38:2354. Upon approval of the plans by the legislative
56 committees and prior to implementation of the plans, in whole or in part, the plans
57 shall be approved by the legislature as provided in R.S. 38:2354(E).
58 (4) Develop procedures in accordance with the Administrative Procedure Act
59 and take actions against any entity, including political subdivisions, to enforce
60 compliance with the comprehensive master upland non coastal area plan. Such
61 procedures and actions may include but are not limited to determinations of
62 noncompliance; appeal from such determinations; the taking of administrative
